textBeforeTable: Bohonan, Terrence - Career Statistics Favorite Food: Buffalo Wings Favorite Movie: 8 Mile Hobbies: UB chillin', Being best friends with Remi   Freshman year...Named Skyline Conference Rookie of the Year. Started 16 games in right field. In 31 games played, he finished with a team-leading 23 RBI's in 70 at-bats with a .314 batting average. Sophomore year...Named First Team All-Skyline, ABCA/Rawlings 3rd Team All-Region and an ABCA/Rawlings Gold Glove winner...Started 41-of-42 games played and held a .342 average at the plate (3rd on team)...Had a team-high 50 hits and 32 RBI...Held an impressive .989 fielding percentage from his outfield position. Junior year...Earned Second Team All-Conference honors...Played in 41 games, while starting 39...Had 47 hits, 25 runs scored and 25 RBI in a team-high 150 at-bats. Senior year...Played in 43-of-44 games...Second on the team in at-bats (123), fourth in triples (2) and fifth in hits (33). Terrence is a 2009 graduate of Patchogue-Medford High School, where he was named All-League during his senior year. He is the son of Fred and Elaine Bohonan.
